OL,3,CBuilder jailed for hammer murder of
OL,4,Cwoman after 'disagreement'
OL,6,FPassing sentence on Wednesday, Judge
OL,7,FChambers said the "brutal and savage"
OL,8,Foffence, involving eight blows to the
OL,9,Fhead, was aggravated by a false
OL,10,Fstatement Norgrove gave police saying
OL,11,Fhis victim was alive and well when he
OL,12,Fleft the property.
OL,14,FThe judge told Norgrove, a former
OL,15,Fpublic sector worker: "You used a
OL,16,Fhammer to repeatedly strike her to the
OL,17,Fhead.
OL,19,F"You were angry because she had
OL,20,Fcontinued to criticise you for your
OL,21,Fchronic delays and workmanship."
